reviews.subject: Introductory Psychology
reviews.review: Dr. Johnson is an excellent professor who really cares about her students. Her lectures are engaging and she is always available to help during office hours.

reviews.subject: Calculus I
reviews.review: Professor Lee's lectures can be dry at times, but he is very knowledgeable and tests fairly. The workload is manageable if you stay on top of the material.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Biology
reviews.review: Dr. Rodriguez is an incredibly passionate and effective teacher. Her labs are well-designed and help cement the concepts from lecture. I would highly recommend taking any of her classes.

reviews.subject: American History Since 1865
reviews.review: Professor Wilson is a knowledgeable and engaging lecturer. His classes are discussion-based, which helps students stay engaged with the material.

reviews.subject: Organic Chemistry
reviews.review: Dr. Chen's lectures can be confusing and she doesn't always explain concepts clearly. The exams are extremely challenging and the workload is very heavy.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Computer Science
reviews.review: Professor Nguyen is very approachable and always willing to help students. The assignments are fair and the class overall is well-structured.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Dr. Gonzalez is an incredibly knowledgeable and passionate professor. Her classes are thought-provoking and she does an excellent job of connecting course material to real-world issues.

reviews.subject: Principles of Marketing
reviews.review: Professor Patel's lectures can be dry and boring at times. The coursework is fairly straightforward, but he doesn't always provide clear guidance on assignments.

reviews.subject: Quantum Mechanics
reviews.review: Dr. Nakamura is an extremely knowledgeable professor who is passionate about the subject matter. Her lectures can be challenging, but she is always willing to provide additional support to help students succeed.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Sociology
reviews.review: Professor Rossi is an engaging and thought-provoking lecturer. Her classes are discussion-based and she encourages students to think critically about social issues.

reviews.subject: General Chemistry
reviews.review: Dr. Hernandez is knowledgeable, but his lectures can be dry and difficult to follow. The course workload is heavy and the exams are challenging.

reviews.subject: Intermediate Spanish
reviews.review: Professor Takahashi is an excellent language instructor. Her classes are engaging and she does a great job of immersing students in the language.

reviews.subject: Introduction to Philosophy
reviews.review: Dr. Monteiro is a brilliant and insightful professor. His lectures are thought-provoking and he encourages students to develop their own philosophical perspectives.

reviews.subject: Macroeconomics
reviews.review: Professor Durand is a knowledgeable and engaging lecturer. Her classes are well-structured and she does a good job of relating course material to current events.

reviews.subject: Molecular Biology
reviews.review: Dr. Patel is a passionate and dedicated professor. His lectures are informative and he provides helpful guidance on lab assignments.

reviews.subject: Intro to Graphic Design
reviews.review: Professor Hernandez is an amazing instructor. Her classes are creative, hands-on, and she provides valuable feedback to help students improve their design skills.

reviews.subject: Differential Equations

reviews.subject: Public Speaking

reviews.subject: Developmental Psychology

reviews.subject: Introduction to Creative Writing
